web
# SIN-63299 — keep the whole web/static/ runtime asset tree in the build
# context. cmd/server/customdomain_wire.go mounts a FileServer on
# `web/static/` and templates reference /static/css/*.css,
# /static/js/*.js, /static/customdomain.css and /static/customdomain.js
# from real production pages. The previous `!web/static/vendor`-only
# exception was tight enough to bring in CHECKSUMS.txt (imported via
# go:embed) but left every other asset off the runtime image, so the
# FileServer 404'd them in staging/prod (auth.css, privacy.css,
# customdomain.css visibly broke /login after SIN-63294). Re-include the
# tree as a whole; there is nothing under web/static/ that is not
# runtime-served.
!web/static
*.md
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
